name: Ring Muscleup
description:
Start in a dead hang with shoulders touching your ears.
Pull yourself up as your hands rotate and when the pull reaches the peak, push your head up and over the rings, while also raising your toes up and push your body up like a normal dip. Complete the muscle up with your elbows in full lock out.

name: Incline Pushup, Narrow Grip
description:
Brace yourself in a push up position against a bench or another elevated platform, with your hands at about shoulder width apart.
Inhale and lower yourself downward until your chest nearly touches. Exhale as you push back up.

name: Seated Leg Raise, V Formation
description:
Sit on the side of a bench and hold on with both hands. Lie back and lift your legs until you are balanced. Your knees should be slightly bent.
Raise your legs while you move your upper body towards your thighs in a V position.

name: Cable Lat Pulldown Leaning Back, Narrow Overhand Grip
description:
Sit down at the machine, adjust the knee pad to your height and secure your knees under the padding. Grab the bar in a narrow grip with your palms facing away from you, slightly more narrow than shoulder width. Extend your arms all the way up and lean back.
Exhale as you bring the bar down until it touches your upper chest. Inhale as you bring the bar back up. Repeat.

name: Barbell Clean & Jerk Step 2: Jerk
description:
Hold the barbell so it's on the top of your chest, and your hands are supporting it with your palms facing up and your elbows out in front of you.
Dip your body by bending your knees and ankles slightly. Explosively drive upward with your legs, driving barbell up, off shoulders. Drop your body down and split one foot forward and other backward as fast as possible, while thrusting your arms over head. The split position places front shin vertical to floor, with front foot flat on floor. The rear knee is slightly bent with rear foot positioned on toes. Return and repeat.

name: Dumbbell Biceps Curl, Preacher
description:
Sit down at the preacher bench and place your upper arms against the arm pad, and grab one dumbbell in each hand, palms facing up.
Raise the dumbbells together until they're almost straight, and then lower back down after a short pause.

name: Cable Crossover, Bent Over
description:
Attach the handles to high pulleys and hold the handles in each hand. Stagger your feet by stepping forward and slightly bend your torso.
Move your arms in a circular motion, by slowly bringing the handles together and cross them over in front of your body. Squeeze your chest as you cross the handles over and slowly lower the weight back to the starting position and repeat.

name: Dumbbell Biceps Curl, On Knee, Underhand Grip
description:
Sit on one side of a bench, hold one dumbbell in one hand with your palm facing up and place that same elbow (extended) against the front of your thigh.
Raise the dumbbell until it reaches shoulder height and slowly lower it back down. Repeat and switch arms after you complete a set.

name: Bench Press, Normal Grip
description:
Lie back on a flat bench. Hold the bar with a normal width grip and hold the bar straight over you.
Breathe in and slowly bring the bar down until it touches your chest. Exhale as you push the bar back to your starting position.

name: Pushup, Wide Grip
description:
Lie on the floor face down with your hands wider than shoulder length apart, while holding your body off the ground with your arms extended.
Inhale and lower yourself downward until your chest nearly touches the floor. Exhale, return to starting position and repeat.

name: Dumbbell Biceps Curl, Incline, Overhand Grip
description:
Sit down on an inclined bench and hold one dumbbell in each hand in an overhand grip with your palms facing down.
Raise both dumbbells together until they reach shoulder level and lower them back down without jerking your upper body.

name: Front Cable Raise, Single Arm
description:
Attach a handle to the low pulley and grasp it in an overhand grip. Stand up straight with your back towards the machine and your feet shoulder width apart.
Exhale as you raise the handle up in an arc until it's above your head. Keep your arm extended and your back straight. Lower and repeat.

name: Cable Triceps Extension, Single Arm, Crossbody
description:
Attach a cable to the middle pulley and stand sideways to the machine with the machine on your right side. Grab the handle in your left and and hold it over your chest.
Exhale as you extend your left arm away from the machine keeping your arm parallel to the floor. Return and repeat.

name: Weighted Situps
description:
Lay back on a flat bench while holding a plate weight against your chest.
With your head pointing straight and forward, raise your body up until you are upright, lifting your shoulders away from the bench. Roll back down to the starting position and repeat.

name: Cable Split Squat
description:
Attach a cable handle to the low pulley. Stand facing the machine with your left foot forward in a lunge. Grab the handle with your left hand while you stand on the front of your right foot. Stand up straight.
Squat down keeping your back straight. Return to start position and repeat. Switch sides when you finish your set.

name: Cross Body Crunch
description:
Lie flat on your back with your knees bent and your feet flat on the floor, with your hands behind your head.
Curl up and twist your left elbow and shoulder up and over your body as if you're trying to touch your right knee. Return and repeat with your right elbow and left knee, alternating each repetition.

name: Dumbbell Fly, Rear Delt
description:
Grasp a pair of dumbbells with a neutral grip (palms facing each other) and stand with your feet shoulder width apart. Bend at the knees and bring your torso forward by bending at the waist. With your head up and eyes forward, the dumbbells should be directly under your chest with your elbows slightly bent.
Exhale as you raise your arms up in an arc, until they are parallel to the floor. Keep a slight bend in your elbows throughout the exercise. Return to start position and repeat.

name: EZ-Bar Triceps Press, Narrow Grip
description:
Lie on a bench with a narrow, overhand grip on the EZ-bar. Position the bar over your forehead with your arms extended.
Lower the bar to your chest by bending your elbows, try to keep your elbows pointing forward. Push back up and repeat.

name: Dip, Machine Assisted
description:
Stand on the bottom step and grasp the handles with a neutral grip. Adjust the weight accordingly (more weight equals more assistance). Start with your elbows bent and your chin tucked in.
Kneel down and inhale as you lower your body and exhale as you push your body up until your arms are fully extended and repeat.

name: Cable Triceps Kickback, Underhand Grip
description:
Stand facing the cable machine and bend down at your hips and knees, keeping your back straight. Grab the handle with one hand, palms facing up. Bend your arm and keep the upper arm close to the body.
Extend your arm behind you by pressing your hand back and straightening your elbow. Keep your arm close to your body. Bend your arm to return to start position and repeat. Then switch sides.

name: Cable Biceps Curl, Seated Leaning Back
description:
Sit at the lateral pulldown machine and attach a rope to the high pulley. Lean back as you extend your arms and hold the rope in a neutral grip.
Exhale as you curl the rope towards your head. Finish the curl with your hands on the rope on either side of your head. Return and repeat.

name: Decline Pushup, Normal Grip
description:
With your hands at about about shoulder width apart, brace yourself in a push up position with your legs resting on an exercise step, bench or box.
Inhale and lower yourself downward until your chest nearly touches the floor. Exhale, return to starting position and repeat.

name: Incline Pushup, Wide Grip
description:
Brace yourself in a push up position against a bench or another elevated platform, with your hands at about about 6 inches wider than shoulder width apart.
Inhale and lower yourself downward until your chest nearly touches. Exhale as you push back up.

name: EZ-Bar Biceps Bottom Half Curl, Preacher, Underhand Grip
description:
Sit down at the preacher bench with your weights in your desired grip type. With your upper arms and chest pressing against the preacher bench pad, extend your arms and hold the weights.
Keep your upper arms still, exhale, and curl the weights upwards while contracting your biceps. Lower the weights to starting position and repeat.

name: Chest Press Machine
description:
Sit down on the machine and select the weight. Grab the handles with an overhand grip and lift your elbows so that your arms are straight, extended and parallel to the floor.
Exhale and push the handles away as you flex your chest. Breathe in and slowly bring the handles towards you.

name: Dumbbell Biceps Curl, Incline Prone, Overhand Grip
description:
With a dumbbell in each hand, lie face down on an incline bench with your shoulders near top of the bench. Let your arms extend and hang naturally in front of you with your palms behind you in an overhand grip.
Raise the dumbbells together and lower them back down while keeping your upper arms still.

name: Dumbbell Shrug, Incline Bench
description:
Lie down on an inclined bench while holding two dumbbells in a neutral grip with your palms facing each other. Keep your feet on the floor to stabilize yourself. Extend your arms down.
Exhale as you raise your shoulders as far up as they can go.

name: Dumbbell Biceps Curl, Standing, Underhand Grip
description:
Stand up straight with a dumbbell in your desired grip, while keeping your elbows close to your sides.
Keep your upper arms still, exhale, and curl the weights upwards, while contracting your biceps. Lower the weights to starting position and repeat.

name: EZ-Bar Biceps Curl, Underhand Wide Grip
description:
Stand up straight with your legs shoulder width apart, while holding the bar in a wide grip. Keep your elbows close to your sides.
Keep your upper arms still, exhale, and curl the bar upwards, while contracting your biceps. Lower the bar to starting position and repeat.

name: Hanging Leg Raise, Windshield Wipers
description:
Hang from a pull up bar.
Raise your legs up so your torso is parallel to the floor. Rotate your legs to one side as far as you can and then rotate to the other side.

name: Cable Squat
description:
Attach a cable handle to the low pulley. Stand facing the machine with your feet a little wider than shoulder width apart. Grab the handle with both of your hands and take a step back.
Squat down keeping your back straight. Return to start position and repeat.

name: Glute Kickback
description:
Kneel down on all fours.
Keeping your leg bent, lift your leg up so your hamstrings are in line with your back, and your foot is in the air. Slowly release back to starting position and repeat, then switch legs.

name: Cable Lat Pulldown, Normal Underhand Grip
description:
Sit down at the machine, adjust the knee pad to your height and secure your knees under the padding. Grab the bar about shoulder width apart. Extend your arms all the way up and lean back slightly with your chest out.
Exhale as you bring the bar down until it touches your upper chest. Inhale as you bring the bar back up. Repeat.

name: Incline Chest Cable Overhead Shrug
description:
Place an incline bench perpendicularly and directly between two cable stacks. Place the handles on the low pulleys. Grab each handle and lay back on the bench. Start with your arms extended and your hands slightly wider than shoulder width apart.
Flex your chest and move your arms together so that your arms are slightly higher and your hands are closer together. The movement is small, so make sure that you feel the tension in your chest at the top of the movement. Return to start position and repeat.

name: Elliptical Machine
description:
Step on pedal platforms and grasp the handle bars on each arm lever. Select "quick start" or enter program.
Pedal forward while alternating the arm levers back and forth.

name: Cable Calf Raise
description:
Attach a cable handle to the low pulley while standing with the front parts of your feet on the edge of an exercise step and your heels hanging off. Hold the cable handle, you can hold the machine with one hand for support if needed.
Keeping your legs straight, flex your calf and raise yourself as high as you can before lowing back to your starting position and repeat.

name: Bench Press, Narrow Grip
description:
Lie back on a flat bench. Hold the bar with a narrow grip and hold the bar straight over you.
Breathe in and slowly bring the bar down until it touches your chest. Exhale as you push the bar back to your starting position.

name: Seated Rope Cable Row
description:
Sit on the bench facing the pulley machine. Grab the rope with both hands, palms facing each other.
Pull the rope back while leaning backwards with your elbows pointed out to your sides. Return to start position and repeat.

name: Cable Biceps Curl, Extended Middle, Underhand Grip
description:
Stand with your feet slightly wider than shoulder width apart. Grab the handles with both hands, palms facing forward and arms straight and parallel to the ground.
Bend your arms at the elbow, bringing your hands up towards your ears. Lower to start position and repeat.

name: Dumbbell Row, Incline Prone
description:
With a dumbbell in each hand, lie face down on an incline bench with your shoulders near top of the bench. Let your arms extend and hang naturally in front of you, with your palms facing backwards.
With your elbows out to the sides, pull the dumbbells up to neck height. Return and repeat.

name: Dumbbell Triceps Extension, Incline Bench, Single Arm, Cross Body
description:
Lie on an incline bench and hold a dumbbell with your left hand in a neutral grip, with your left arm extended upwards. Lay your right hand across your stomach.
Inhale as you lower the dumbbell by bending your elbow, bringing the dumbbell down sideways over your chest in an arc. Keep your upper arm as still as possible. Exhale, return and repeat and switch sides when you finish this set.

name: Cable Fly, Diagonal High & Low
description:
Attach a handle to the low pulley on one side and the high pulley on the other side. Stand between the pulleys with your arms extended.
Slowly pull the handles diagonally, until your wrists cross over.

name: Machine Biceps Curl, Single Arm
description:
Sit down at the preacher machine bench and grab the handle with a single arm. With your upper arms and chest pressing against the preacher bench pad, extend your arm and hold the handle.
Keep your upper arms still, exhale, and curl the handle upwards while contracting your biceps. Lower the weights to starting position and repeat. Switch hands once you finish the set.

name: Dumbbell Row, Single Arm, Neutral Grip
description:
Place a dumbbell on either side of a flat bench. Put your right leg on the top of the bench near the end, while placing your right hand at the end of the bench for support. Grab the dumbbell with your left hand in a neutral grip (palms facing your stomach). Keep your lower back straight.
Exhale as you pull the weight up to your chest while keeping your arm close to your side. Inhale as you lower and repeat. Switch sides when you finish.

name: Dumbbell Fly
description:
Lie down on a flat bench with a dumbbell in each hand, resting on top of your thighs with your palms facing each other. Use your thighs to lift up the dumbbells with your palms facing each other and extend your arms out to your sides, with a slight bend in your elbows and stretch in your chest.
Exhale and bring the dumbbells up and together in a wide arc. Return to starting position and repeat.

name: Dumbbell Biceps Curl, Preacher, Neutral Grip
description:
Sit down at the preacher bench and place your upper arms against the arm pad, and grab one dumbbell in each hand, palms facing each other.
Raise the dumbbells together until they're almost straight, and then lower back down after a short pause.

name: Incline Pushup, Normal Grip
description:
Brace yourself in a push up position against a bench, or another elevated platform, with your hands at about shoulder width apart.
Inhale and lower yourself downward until your chest nearly touches. Exhale as you push back up.

name: Bodyweight Pull Up, Narrow Grip
description:
Hold on to the pull up bar using a narrow grip (slightly more narrow than shoulder width). Hang there with your body extended.
Exhale as you pull yourself up until your neck reaches the height of your hands. Inhale as you lower your body until your arms and shoulders are extended and repeat.

name: Reverse Cable Triceps Extension, Single Arm
description:
Stand with your back facing the machine and your legs slightly bent, shoulder width apart. With one hand grab the pulley so your elbow is bent out in front of you and your hand is behind your shoulder.
Straighten your arm out in front of you, keeping your arm lifted. Bend your arm back to start position and repeat. Then switch arms.

name: Cable Fly
description:
Position a flat bench between two low pulleys. Make sure when you lay on it, your chest is lined up with the cable pulleys. Lay flat on the bench, keeping your feet on the ground. Have someone give you the handles for each hand. Grab each handle with your palms facing up. Extend your arms to your side, parallel to the floor while keeping a slight bend in your elbows.
Lift your arms above you, bringing your two hands together out in front of your chest. Keep a slight bend to your elbows.

name: Hanging Leg Raise, Scissor Kicks
description:
Start by hanging from a chin-up bar, using either a wide grip or a medium grip.
Raise your legs straight in front without swinging the body. Hold your legs out and perform small, controlled, scissor kicks using the lower abs.

name: Machine Row, Wide Grip
description:
Adjust the seat and chest pad to the correct height and select your weight. Grab the wider handles while keeping your back straight.
Exhale as you pull the handles towards you. Inhale as you return to start position and repeat.

name: Standing Cable Row, Single Arm, High
description:
Stand facing the pulley machine. Attach the cable handle to the high pulley. Stand up straight and hold the handle in your left hand with an overhand grip and extend your arm.
Exhale as you pull the handle towards your chest as far in as possible. Return and repeat.

name: Decline Dumbbell Bench Press, Normal Grip
description:
Lie down on a decline bench with a dumbbell in each hand resting on top of your thighs with your palms facing each other. Use your thighs to lift up the dumbbells one at a time so they are over your chest, shoulder width apart.
Breathe out and push the dumbbells up using your chest.

name: Step Machine
description:
Step onto pedal platforms and grasp hand rails. Select "quick start" or enter program.
Place your bodyweight on one pedal and allow other pedal to raise. Before the lower step hits the bottom or upper step hits top, alternate with opposite movement. Repeat.

name: Dumbbell Triceps Extension, Behind Neck, Single Arm
description:
Sit down on an upright bench while grasping a dumbbell in your right hand. Lift the dumbbell up so it's positioned slightly behind your head with your arm outstretched (or have a spotter hand it to you).
While keeping your upper arm stationary, lower the dumbbell sideways in an arc just behind your head. Return and repeat.

name: Decline Cable Fly, Single Arm
description:
Move the cables to a high position and stand with your feet hip distance apart. Grab the cable with one hand, palms facing down.
Keeping your arm straight, pull the cable down and across your body so your hand is at your opposite hip. Bring your arm back to start position and repeat.

name: Dumbbell Biceps Curl, Preacher, Single Arm, Neutral Grip
description:
Sit down at the preacher bench and place your upper arms against the arm pad, and grab a dumbbell in one hand.
Raise the dumbbell until your forearm is almost straight and then lower it back down after a short pause. Repeat and switch arms when you finish your set.

name: Standing Cable Row, Middle
description:
Stand facing the pulley machine. Attach the cable bar to the middle pulley. Hold the bar with an overhand grip and extend your arms.
Keeping your back straight, exhale as you bring the bar to your chest. Return to start position and repeat.

name: Seated Leg Raise
description:
Sit on the floor or a bench with your legs bent. Lean back slightly and pull your knees into your chest.
Push your legs out until they are extended while stabilizing yourself with your hands. As you kick out, gently lean back a bit. Return and repeat.

name: Decline Dumbbell Bench Press, Wide Grip
description:
Secure your legs and lie down on a decline bench with a dumbbell in each hand, resting on top of your thighs with your palms facing each other. Use your thighs to lift up the dumbbells one at a time, so they are over your chest, shoulder width apart. Hold the dumbbells in your desired grip about 6 inches wider than shoulder length apart.
Breathe out and push the dumbbells up using your chest.

name: Glute Kickback Machine
description:
Select your weight and stand on the glute kickback machine with your hands on the stabilizing bar and keep the back of your left leg against the supporting pad roller.
With your right leg and arms supporting your weight, exhale and kickback your left leg against the machine. Fully extend your leg behind you and bring it back in as you inhale and repeat.

name: Cable Pull, High & Low Together
description:
Stand between two cable stacks. Attach a handle to the high pulley to your right and a handle to the low pulley behind you. Face the high pulley and grab it with your right hand and the low pulley with your left hand. Extend your arms to that your right arm is in front of you over your head and your left is behind you and below you.
Exhale as you swing your arms in oppostite directions while you are keeping your arms straight. Twist with your shoulders. Return and repeat.

name: Decline Dumbbell Fly
description:
Secure your legs and lie down on a decline bench, with a dumbbell in each hand.
Exhale and bring the dumbbells up and together in a wide arc. Return to starting position and repeat.

name: Kettlebell Clean and Jerk Single Arm
description:
Start by standing over the kettlebell with your feet a bit wider than shoulder width. Squat down over the kettlebell and and grab it with one hand in an overhand grip.
Pull the kettlebell off the ground while thrusting your hips and knees. When the kettlebell leaves the ground, fluidly bring it up to your shoulder before thrusting it up and over your head with an extended arm, while exploding upwards with your legs. Bring the kettlebell down carefully return and repeat.

name: Cable Biceps Curl, Incline Prone, Underhand Grip
description:
Lay face down on the incline bench and grab the bar with both hands, palms facing away from you, keeping your arms straight.
Bend your arms at the elbows, lifting your hands up towards your chest. Lower and repeat.

name: Dumbbell Triceps Extension, Decline Bench, Single Arm, Cross Body
description:
Lie on a decline bench and hold a dumbbell with your left hand in a neutral grip, with your left arm extended upwards. Lay your right hand across your stomach.
Inhale as you lower the dumbbell by bending your elbow, bringing the dumbbell down sideways over your chest in an arc. Keep your upper arm as still as possible. Exhale, return and repeat, and switch sides when you finish this set.

name: Incline Dumbbell Pullover, Bent Arm
description:
Lie down on an incline bench with a dumbbell securely grasped between both of your hands, palms facing each other. With your feet firmly planted on the floor or bench supports, raise the dumbbell up over your chest with your arms extended.
Keep your arms straight and lower the weight behind your head in an arc movement, as you breathe in. Extend until you feel a stretch in your chest, exhale as you return the weight to the starting position and repeat.

name: Leg Raise, Straight Legs
description:
Position yourself in a captain's chair with your back and forearms on the pads and your hands gripping the handles. Extend your legs so they are hanging towards the floor.
Exhale as you raise your legs as high as you can while keeping them straight. Return to start position and repeat. Make sure that you're not cheating with the momentum.

name: Upright Cable Rotation
description:
Stand facing a cable machine and attach the handle to the middle pulley. Grab the pulley with your right hand and position your bent elbow at shoulder height and out to the side, with your forearm in line with the cable (palm facing down).
Exhale as you pull the handle as far back as possible in an arc, until your hand is about head height. Return and repeat.

name: Twist
description:
Lie flat on a mat with your arms outstretched to the sides and your palms on the floor. Lift your legs up straight so they are perpendicular to the floor.
Keeping your legs straight and together, twist them to the left until you feel a stretch and then twist to the right side and repeat.

name: Side Bend
description:
Position yourself sideways on a hyperextension bench, with your arms crossed over your chest. Make sure that your hips, feet and legs are secure against the appropriate padding and foot rests.
Lower your torso to the side as far as it can go, while keeping your legs straight. Rise up so that your chest is above your torso. Return to start position and repeat. When you have finished your set, switch sides.

name: Machine Calf Press
description:
Sit down at an upright leg press machine with the front of your feet on the foot rest. Hold onto the support handles.
Exhale as you push forward with the front of your feet using your calves. Return and repeat.

name: Cable Lats Chest Twist
description:
Stand between two pulley machines and attach the handles to the middle pulleys. Grab both handles and turn your body so that you are facing the machine that your left hand is connected to. Extend your left arm while allowing your right arm to be pulled back to your chest.
Exhale as you reverse the positioning of the handles in a continuous fluid motion. Continue until you finish your set.

name: Cable Wrist Curl, Overhand Grip
description:
Attach a straight bar to the low pulley. Grab the bar in an overhand grip with your palms facing down and your arms extended down, while standing with a straight back.
Exhale and curl your wrists upwards. Inhale and lower your wrists back to your starting position. Repeat while keeping your forearms still.

name: Upright Cable Row, Single Arm
description:
Attach the cable handle to the low pulley and grab it in an overhand grip with your left hand. Stand with feet shoulder width apart.
Pull the cable up, with your elbow out to the side until your hand is at about chin height. Return and repeat. Switch arms when you finish your set.

name: Barbell Rollout, On Knees
description:
Place round 5 or 10lb weights on either side of a barbell and kneel on the floor facing it.
Slowly lean forward with your hands gripping the barbell, shoulder width apart. Push the barbell forward in a straight motion that stretches your body forward. Once your body is stretched out, slowly pull yourself back to starting position.

name: Decline Dumbbell Bench Press, Rotating Grip
description:
Secure your legs and lie down on a decline bench with a dumbbell in each hand resting on top of your thighs, with your palms facing each other. Use your thighs to lift up the dumbbells one at a time, so they are over your chest, shoulder width apart. Hold the dumbbells with your palms facing each other, shoulder width apart.
Breathe out and push the dumbbells up using your chest. As you press up, rotate your wrists so that when you fully extend your arms your grip is overhand rather than neutral. Return to start position by rotating your hands back to a neutral grip and repeating.

name: Ring Pushups
description:
Adjust the height of your rings for your fitness level (the lower the rings the more difficult the exercise). Grip the rings and place yourself in the pushup position with your body straight and your arms extended out in front of you.
Inhale as you lower your body and exhale as you push back up.

name: Cable Woodchopper
description:
Stand sideways next to a cable machine with the machine on your right and attach the rope to the low pulley. Grab the rope with both hands and extend your arms, the rope should be slightly to the right of your right leg.
Exhale as you twist the rope up and to the left in a gradual arc, until your hands are at the same height as your head. Return and repeat and then switch sides.

name: Kettlebell 2 Handed Swing
description:
Hold the kettlebell with two hands as you slightly bend at the hips, keeping your back straight. The kettlebell should be just in front of your hips, between your legs.
Thrust your hips forward and keep your knees straight, so that the kettlebell is pushed forward and upward and push it over your head, while keeping your head forward and squeezing your glutes. Allow the kettlebell to swing back down. As the kettlebell approaches the lower swing, bend at your hips and knees. Your forearm will make contact with your inner thigh, allowing the kettlebell to swing back under your hips. Repeat as many repetitions as you need to in a fluid motion.

name: Barbell Shoulder Press, Wide Grip
description:
Sit down on a shoulder press bench and grab onto the bar.
Keeping a straight back, exhale and press the bar upward until your arms are extended overhead. Lower in front of your head until the bar touches your upper chest and repeat.

name: Abduction Machine
description:
Sit down on the abductor machine and select a comfortable weight. Position your legs and grip the handles on each side. From the waist up, your body should be stationary.
Slowly press against the machine with your legs to move them away from each other while exhaling. Inhale while releasing and repeat.

name: Cable Triceps Pushdown, Underhand Grip
description:
Attach the bar to the high pulley. Hold the bar in an underhand grip with your arms so your hands are just below your chest while facing the machine.
Exhale as you push down with your triceps, keeping your arms close to your sides. Return to start position and repeat.

name: Dumbbell Biceps Curl, Incline Preacher, Underhand Grip
description:
Stand behind an inclined bench and rest one arm on the back support, while holding a dumbbell, palm facing up.
Only moving your lower arm, raise the dumbbell up to your shoulder and lower it back down.

name: EZ-Bar Biceps Curl, Preacher, Underhand Grip
description:
Sit down at the preacher bench and grab the bar using your desired grip type. With your upper arms and chest pressing against the preacher bench pad, extend your arms and hold the bar.
Keep your upper arms still, exhale, and curl the bar upwards while contracting your biceps. Lower the bar to starting position and repeat.

name: Reverse Cable Tricep Crossover
description:
Stand with your feet shoulder width apart. Crossing your arms in front of you, grab opposite handle with each hand. Keep your back straight.
Keep your elbows stationary and extend your arms down simultaneously to your sides. Be sure not to lock your elbows as you straighten your arms. Slowly bend your arms back to start position and repeat.

name: Cable Torso Twist
description:
Attach the cable handle to the medium pulley and stand with your right side facing the machine. Step away from the machine and turn your lower body. Grab the handle with both hands. Lift the heel of your nearest leg from the floor. Twist away from the machine until your right arm is straight in line with the cable and you're facing away from the machine.
Keeping your arms straight, rotate your torso to the other side until the cable makes contact with your shoulder. Return to start position and repeat. When you have finished your set, switch sides.

name: Dumbbell Biceps Curl, Incline, Alternating, Overhand Grip
description:
Sit down on an inclined bench and hold one dumbbell in each hand in an overhand grip with your palms facing down.
Start by raising one dumbbell until they reach shoulder level and lower them back down without jerking your upper body.

name: Situps with Weight Above Head
description:
Lay back on a flat bench while holding a plate weight against your chest. Extend your arms out straight and hold the weight out in front of you.
With your head pointing straight and forward, raise your body up until you are upright, lift your shoulders away from the bench. As you pull your body up, move the plate weight so it is above your head when you become upright. Roll back down to the starting position and repeat.

name: Cable Biceps Curl, Extended Low, Single Arm, Underhand Grip
description:
Stand with your feet a bit wider than shoulder width apart. With one hand, grab the handle, palm facing up.
Bend your arm at the elbow, lower to start position and repeat, then switch arms.

name: Incline Prone Dumbbell Fly
description:
Lean into an inclined bench while holding two dumbbells in a neutral grip with your palms facing each other. Keep your toes on the floor to stabilize yourself. Keep your lower back straight and extend your arms down.
Exhale as you move the weights up and away from you in an arc, until your arms are parallel to the floor. Be sure to squeeze your shoulder blades together. Return to start position and repeat.

name: Dumbbell Triceps Extension, Flat Bench
description:
Lie on a flat bench and hold a dumbbell with two hands over your head with arms extended.
Inhale as you lower the dumbbell by bending your elbows until the dumbbell is behind your head. Keep your upper arms as still as possible. Exhale, return and repeat.

name: Weighted Pull Up, Wide Grip
description:
Add weight using a dip belt or by placing a dumbbell between your ankles. Hold on to the pull up bar using a wide grip (a few inches wider than shoulder width apart). Hang there with your body extended.
Exhale as you pull yourself up until your neck reaches the height of your hands. Inhale as you lower your body until your arms and shoulders are extended and repeat.

name: Cable Deadlift
description:
Bring an exercise step to the front of the pulley machine and attach the cable bar to the low pulley. Hold the bar in a normal, overhand grip and bend your knees and body forward while keeping a straight back.
Exhale as you push up and lift the bar with your legs and at the same time bringing your torso to an upright position. Once you are standing, push your chest out and bring your shoulder blades back so you are standing upright at attention. Return and repeat.

name: Machine Biceps Curl
description:
Sit down with your arms pressed against the pads and grab the handles in your desired grip type.
Keep your upper arms still, exhale, and curl the handles upwards while contracting your biceps and repeat. Only lower the weights all the way down once you are finished with the exercise.

name: Cable Triceps Extension, Behind Neck, Single Arm
description:
Place a bench sideways in front of the machine and attach a cable handle to the low pulley. Hold the handle in your left hand with your right side facing the machine. Start with your left hand behind your neck while your elbow is positioned upward.
Exhale and extend your left arm while keeping your upper arm straight and still. Return and repeat.

name: Hanging Leg Raise, Obliques
description:
Hang from a pull up bar with your arms extended.
Exhale as you raise your legs up, while bending at the knees and twisting until they're about parallel to the floor. Alternate directions for each repetition.

name: Cable Rotation, External
description:
Stand with your left side facing the machine. With your right hand, grab the handle, keeping your elbow close to your body and your hand in front of your stomach.
Bring your arm back as far as you can, keeping your elbow close to your body. Return to start position and repeat.

name: Cable Shoulder Press, Cuban
description:
Stand between to cable stacks and attach the handles to the low pulleys. Stand with your forearms parallel to the floor, and your hands raised with your palms facing forward.
Exhale, press your hands up and bring your arms back to the starting position, and rotate your shoulders so that your hands are pointing towards the floor and your palms are facing back. Return and repeat.

name: Dumbbell Horizontal Row, Incline Prone
description:
With a dumbbell in each hand, lie face down on an incline bench with your shoulders near top of the bench. Extend your arms forward with your palms facing the ground.
Exhale as you pull your arms back so they are outstretched to your sides. During this movement, rotate your wrists so that your palms are facing forward when you finish the movement. Return and repeat.

name: Lateral Cable Raise, Bent over, Single Arm
description:
Stand sideways next to a cable stack and attach the handle to the low pulley. With the machine to your right, grasp the handle with your left hand and bend over slightly at the waist.
Exhale as you raise your arm to the side until elbow is at shoulder height. Lower and repeat. When you finish the set, repeat with your other arm.

name: Barbell Shrug
description:
Stand with your feet shoulder width apart holding a barbell with a overhand grip.
Exhale as you raise your shoulders as far up as they can go. Return and repeat.

name: Leg Press Machine
description:
Sit on the machine with your back on the padded support. Place feet on platform and extend your hips and knees. Release dock lever and grasp the support handles on the sides.
Lower sled by flexing hips and knees. Return by extending.

name: Cable Wrist Curl, Underhand Grip
description:
Attach a straight bar to the low pulley. Grab the bar in an underhand grip with your palms facing up and your arms extended down, while standing with a straight back.
Exhale and curl your wrists upwards. Inhale and lower your wrists back to your starting position. Repeat while keeping your forearms still.

name: Barbell Snatch
description:
Start by grabbing a barbell with a wider than shoulder width, overhand grip. Keep your hips and knees slightly bent and your back flat.
Exhale as you push your feet into the floor and pull the barbell up to rest just above your knees. Extend your knees and thrust your hips, as you explosively drive the barbell towards the ceiling, while shrugging your shoulders to create momentum to propel the barbell. Next, extend your arms over your head as you drop your hips to place your body underneath the bar. Push your feet into the floor and extend your hips to stand. Return and repeat.

name: Situps
description:
Lie on your back with your knees bent and your feet flat on the floor.
Place your finger tips behind your ears with your elbows out to the side.
With your head pointing straight and forward, raise your body up towards your knees, lifting your shoulders off the floor. Lean back down to start position and repeat.

name: Dumbbell Side Bend
description:
Stand up straight with a dumbbell in your right hand, while holding it in a neutral grip. Place your left hand on your hip.
Bend over at the waist to the right as far as possible. Return to start position and repeat. When you have finished your set, switch sides.

name: Bodyweight Muscle Up
description:
Start by hanging from a pull-up bar.
Pull yourself up (chin to the bar), 'roll' your chest over the bar as a transition from a pull-up to a dip and press your hands down and push your body upwards to complete a dip.

name: Reverse Cable Fly, Bent Over
description:
Stand between two cable stacks and attach the handles to the low pulleys. Bend over at the waist and grab the left handle with your right hand and vice versa. Keep your feet slightly apart.
Exhale as you lift your upper arms to the side. Lower and repeat.

name: Cable Standing Chest Press
description:
Position dual pulleys to chest height and choose your weight. Stand a foot or two in front of the cables, holding one in each hand. Stagger your balance for better stability with one foot in front of the other. Position your upper arms with your shoulder blades together.
Hold your body still, as you press the handles forward in front of you and bring them together at full extension. Return to starting position and repeat.

name: Dip, Bench Assisted
description:
Place a bench behind your back. Hold on to the bench on its edge with the hands fully extended, separated at shoulder width. Extend your legs forward resting on the floor.
Inhale as you lower your body by bending at your elbows. Press back up to starting position with your triceps and repeat.

name: Cable Lat Pulldown Row, Seated Narrow Overhand Grip
description:
Sit down at the machine, adjust the knee pad to your height and secure your knees under the padding. Grab the bar with your palms facing away from you slightly more narrow than shoulder width. Extend your arms all the way up and lean back slightly with your chest out.
Exhale as you bring the bar down while leaning back into a row. Inhale and lean back up as you bring the bar back up. Repeat.

name: Stability Ball Pike
description:
Place your stomach on the ball and roll forward until your hands touch the floor. Walk your hands in front of you until your shins are on the ball. Keep your hands a bit wider than shoulder width apart, in a pushup position.
Keeping your legs straight, lift your hips up, pulling the ball towards your body so your butt is up in the air. Lower back down to starting position and repeat.

name: Incline Dumbbell Bench Press, Narrow Grip
description:
Secure your legs and lie down on an incline bench with a dumbbell in each hand, resting on top of your thighs with your palms facing each other. Use your thighs to lift up the dumbbells one at a time so they are over your chest shoulder width apart. Hold the dumbbells in your desired grip about 2 inches or so in from shoulder length apart.
Breathe out and push the dumbbells up using your chest.

name: Standing Cable Row, Single Arm, Low
description:
Stand facing the pulley machine. Attach the cable handle to the low pulley. Bend down slightly and hold the handle in your left hand, with an overhand grip and extend your arm while bracing yourself with your right hand on your right thigh.
Exhale as you pull the handle towards your chest as far in as possible. Return and repeat.

name: Lateral Cable Raise
description:
Stand between two cable stacks and attach handles to the low pulleys. Grasp the left handle with your right hand and vice versa.
With elbows slightly bent, exhale as you raise both arms to the side until your elbows are at shoulder height. Lower and repeat.

name: Reverse Cable Fly, Single Arm
description:
Stand with your left side facing a cable pulley machine. Attach the handle to the medium pulley. With your right hand, grab the handle and reach across your torso with it.
Exhale and pull the handle all the way until your right arm is extended and outstretched to your right side. Keep your hand at shoulder height the entire time. Return and repeat. Switch sides when you finish your set.

name: Barbell Clean & Jerk
description:
Stand over a barbell with the front of your feet positioned under the bar, slightly wider apart than hip width apart. Squat down and grip the bar with an overhand grip slightly wider than shoulder width apart. Position your shoulders over the bar with your back arched tightly. Keep your arms straight with your elbows lined up over the bar.
Lift the bar up and off the floor by extending your hips and knees. As bar reaches your knee height, aggressiveliy lift your shoulders while keeping barbell close to your thighs. When the barbell passes mid-thigh, allow it to touch your thighs. Thrust upward extending your body. Shrug shoulders and pull barbell upward with arms, allowing your elbows to flex out to sides while keeping the bar close to body. Aggressively pull your body under the bar, while rotating your elbows around bar. Catch the bar on your shoulders while moving into squat position. When you reach the bottom of your squat, immediately thrust up. Next, dip your body by bending your knees and ankles slightly. Explosively drive upward with legs, driving barbell up off shoulders. Drop your body downward and split one foot forward and other backward as fast as possible, while thrusting your arms over head. The split position places front shin vertical to floor with front foot flat on floor. Keep the rear knee slightly bent with your rear foot positioned on toes. Return and repeat.

name: Bicycle Crunch
description:
Lie on the floor with your legs straight out and hands behind your head.
Raise your legs and touch your right elbow to your left knee, while extending your right leg, creating a motion like you are on a bicycle.

name: Dumbbell Scarecrow
description:
Grab two dumbbells in an overhand grip and hold them up to your sides and keep your back straight.
Lower the dumbbells by twisting your arms in an arc downwards. Exhale and raise them back to start position and repeat.

name: Hanging Leg Raise, Knees to Elbows
description:
Start by hanging from a chin-up bar, using either a wide grip or a medium grip.
Tuck your knees up toward your elbows. Then slowly lower your legs back down. Beginners may not be able to raise their knees all the way up to their elbows.

name: Incline Cable Fly
description:
Position an incline bench between two low pulleys. Make sure when you lay on it, your chest is lined up with the cable pulleys. Lay flat on the bench, keeping your feet on the ground. Extend your arms to your side, parallel to the floor while keeping a slight bend in your elbows.
Lift your arms in front of you, bringing your two hands together out in front of your chest. Keep a slight bend to your elbows.

name: Cable Triceps Pushdown, Single Arm
description:
Attach a handle to the high pulley. Hold the handle with your right hand so your hand is just below your chest while facing the machine.
Exhale as you push down with your triceps, keeping your right arm close to your side. Return to start position and repeat. Switch sides when you finish your set.

name: Crossfit Situp
description:
Sit with your feet together and your knees out wide to the side. Have your hands one on top of the other, forming a triangle with your arms, and touch your shoes.
Keeping your arms in a triangle, with your hands layered on top of each other, lean backwards until your back is on the floor. Keep your feet together and knees wide. Sit back up to the starting position and repeat.

name: Cable Crossover
description:
Adjust the pulleys to the highest point possible on both sides and attach a single grip handle to each. Grasp each handle with your palms facing down. Take a step forward. Your arms should be slightly bent at the elbows.
Slowly bring the handles together and cross them over in front of your body, while rotating only your shoulders. Slowly lower the weight back to start position and repeat.

name: Decline Bench Press, Normal Grip
description:
Lie back on a decline bench. Hold the bar with a normal grip straight over you.
Breathe in and slowly bring the bar down until it touches your chest. Exhale as you push the bar back to your starting position. Hold the bar there for a second and repeat.

name: Bodyweight Lats Inverted Plank
description:
Start by holding on to one of the neutral chin up bars with both hands in a close, overhand grip.
As you pulll your body up, lean back and thrust your legs forward so that your body is briefly parallel to the floor. Return and repeat.

name: Incline Dumbbell Overhead Shrug
description:
Lie down on an incline bench with a dumbbell in each hand, resting on top of your thighs with your palms facing each other. Use your thighs to lift up the dumbbells straight up until your arms are extended and straight up.
Flex your chest and move your arms together so that your arms are slightly higher and your hands are closer together. The movement is small, so make sure that you feel the tension in your chest at the top of the movement. Return to start position and repeat.

name: Bodyweight Pull Up into Row
description:
Hang from the pull up bar with your palms facing each other.
Start by raising your legs up as if you were doing a hanging leg raise movement. As you lift yourself, pull your upper body back to a horizontal position and do a pull-up row from there. Return and repeat.

name: Ab Machine
description:
Sit down at the ab machine and grab the top handles.
Breathe out while crunching your upper torso in a slow and concentrated movement.

name: Hand Walk to Push Up
description:
Stand bent over with your fingers touching the floor just above your toes.
Walk your body down into a pushup position, do a pushup, return and repeat.

name: Cable Pullover
description:
Stand facing the pulley machine, feet shoulder width apart. Grab the rope with both hands, with a slight bend in your elbows and step away from the machine so there is some resistance. Bend your knees slightly, keep your back straight.
Pull the rope down towards your knees, keeping your back straight and arms slightly bent. Return to start position and repeat.

name: Leg Raise Machine
description:
Sit on the machine with your back against the padded back support. Place your legs under the padded lever. Grasp the handles on the sides for support.
Push the padded lever up by extending your knees until your legs are straight. Return and Repeat.

name: Side Plank
description:
Lay on your side with one forearm flat on the ground. Prop your body off the floor, lifting your hips until your body is in a straight line from your ankles to your shoulders. Your feet should be stacked one on top of the other and your free hand straight up in the air.
Hold position.

name: Cable Biceps Curl, Single Arm, Underhand Grip
description:
Stand with your feet shoulder width apart. With one hand, grab the handle palm facing you, keeping your arm straight.
Bend your arm at the elbow, lifting your hand up towards your chest. Lower and repeat, then switch arms.

name: Barbell Deadlift
description:
Stand with in front of a loaded barbell and bend your knees and body forward. Grab the bar with an overhand grip with your hands just over shoulder width apart.
Exhale as you push up and lift the bar with your legs and at the same time bring your torso to an upright position. Once you are standing, push your chest out and bring your shoulder blades back so you are standing upright at attention. Return while keeping your legs straight and make sure the barbell touches the floor before starting your next rep.

name: Standing Cable Row, Cross Body
description:
Stand between two shoulder-high cable pulleys (adjustable cross-over machine). Grasp right stirrup with left hand and left stirrup with right hand at chest height, with your arms extended.
Exhale as you pull both handles by moving elbows back to your sides. Keep upper arms horizontal. Return and repeat.

name: Decline Situps
description:
Anchor your feet to top of a decline bench and slowly roll back into starting position. Cross your arms over your chest or place your hands behind your ears.
Exhale and bring yourself up until your upper body is perpendicular to the ground. Lower yourself back to the starting position while inhaling and repeat.

name: Cable Shrug
description:
Attach a cable bar to the low pulley. Hold the bar in an overhand grip with your arms extended while facing the machine.
Exhale as you raise your shoulders as far up as they can go. Return and repeat.

name: Dumbbell Triceps Extension, Seated
description:
Sit down on an upright bench while grasping a dumbbell with both hands. Lift the dumbbell up so it's positioned slightly behind your head with your arms outstretched (or have a spotter hand it to you).
While keeping your arms close to your head, lower the weight behind your head. Keep your upper arms stationary and return and repeat.

name: Cable Triceps Extension, Behind Neck, Facing Away
description:
Attach the rope to a high pulley and take a step away from the machine. Hold the rope in a neutral grip just behind your head. Lean into the step while making sure your back is straight.
Exhale as you extend your forearms until your elbows are straight. Return and repeat.

name: Cable Scarecrow, Single Arm
description:
Stand facing a cable machine and attach the handle to the low pulley. Grab the pulley with your right hand and hold your arm out to the side, with your hand down.
Exhale as you raise the handle by twisting your arm in an arc upwards. Inhale as you lower and then repeat.

name: Dumbbell Front Raise
description:
Stand with your feet shoulder width apart holding two dumbbells in an overhand grip.
Exhale as you lift the dumbbells forward in an arc until they are just above the height of your shoulders. Return and repeat.

name: Adduction Machine
description:
Sit down so your feet are on the foot rests, knees are bent, pads are on the inside of your knees, legs are apart, and your back is straight against pad behind you.
Use your inner thighs to push your legs together against the pads, while breathing out. Slowly bring the legs back out and repeat.

name: EZ-Bar Shoulder Highpull
description:
Stand holding the EZ-bar with a normal overhand grip.
Exhale as you pull the bar up to neck height. Lead with your elbows and let your wrists flex as the bar rises. Lower and repeat.

name: Cable Biceps Curl, Overhand Grip
description:
Stand with your feet shoulder width apart and grab the bar with both hands, while keeping your arms straight.
Bend your arms at the elbows, lifting your hands up towards your chest. Lower and repeat.

name: Decline Cable Fly
description:
Position a decline bench between two low pulleys. Make sure when you lay on it, your chest is lined up with the cable pulleys. Lay flat on the bench, keeping your feet on the ground. Extend your arms to your side, parallel to the floor while keeping a slight bend in your elbows.
Lift your arms above you, bringing your two hands together out in front of your chest. Keep a slight bend to your elbows.

name: Power Pushup, With Clap
description:
Lie on the floor face down with your hands just wider than shoulder length apart while, holding your body off the ground with your arms extended.
Start the pushup normally and pause at the bottom position for a second. Push back up with so much power that your hands leave the ground for enough time to do a clap in between.

name: Dumbbell Shoulder Press, Military Seated
description:
Sit down on a bench holding dumbbells in either hand in a neutral grip at about neck height.
Exhale and press the dumbbells up. As your press up, rotate the grips in your hands so that when they reach the top, your hands are in an overhand grip with your palms facing forward. Return, twisting back to neutral, and repeat.

name: Bridge, Bodyweight
description:
Lie on your back with your knees bent, feet flat on the floor and hands by your side.
Tighten your abs and butt to lift your hips off the ground. Try to create a straight line from knees to shoulders. Lower back down to start position and repeat.

name: Dumbbell Biceps Curl, Seated, Underhand Grip
description:
Sit down on a bench and hold one dumbbell in each hand in an underhand grip with your palms facing up.
Raise both dumbbells together until they reach shoulder level, and lower them back down without jerking your upper body.

name: Dumbbell Lateral Raise, Incline Bench
description:
Sit down on an incline bench holding a dumbbell in either hand in a neutral grip, arms are extended by your sides.
Exhale as you raise your arms until your elbows are shoulder height, return and repeat.

name: Hamstrings Machine
description:
Select your weight and sit down on the machine with your ankles on top of the bar. Brace yourself by gripping the stabilizer bar with your hands.
Exhale and curl your legs in while pressing your ankles against the bar. Inhale as you extend your legs slightly lower than your starting position. You should feel tension in your muscles during the whole movement.

name: Cable Leg Curl
description:
Attach the foot harness to one ankle and grab the support bar. Put all weight in your free leg and slightly bend your leg attached to the harness.
Pull the cable back by bending your knee behind you. Return to starting position by straightening your knee and repeat, then switch legs.

name: Cable Biceps Curl Supported by Incline Bench
description:
Lie face down on an incline bench in front of the cable pulley with your shoulders near top of the bench. Grab the bar in your desired grip and extend your arms.
Curl the bar up to your shoulders, and return to starting position and repeat.

name: Chest Fly Machine, Palm Press
description:
Sit down at the machine with your back against the pad. With your forearms parallel to the ground, position your palms on the pads.
Exhale as you press the handles together.

name: Dumbbell Biceps Curl, Incline, Underhand Grip
description:
Sit down on an inclined bench and hold one dumbbell in each hand in an underhand grip with your palms facing up.
Raise both dumbbells together until they reach shoulder levels and lower them back down without jerking your upper body.

name: Decline Oblique Situps
description:
Start by securing your legs at the end of a decline bench and slowly lay down on the bench with your hands behind your head and elbows outstretched.
Exhale as you pull yourself up and twist so that your right elbow touches your left knee at the top. Return and repeat with your left elbow and right knee, alternating each repetition.

name: Calf Raise, Single Leg
description:
Do this exercise while holding on to a bar or rack with your hand. Place the front part of one foot on an exercise step, with your heel hanging off. Raise your other foot up and cross it behind your other calf.
Keeping your leg that is supporting you straight, flex your calf and raise yourself as high as you can, and then lower to start position and repeat.

name: Assisted Pull Up Machine
description:
Start by setting your weight. Stand on the side platforms while you hold the pull up handles. Carefully put both your knees onto the the padded knee rest.
Exhale as you pull yourself up. Inhale as you lower your body until your arms and shoulders are extended and repeat.

name: Barbell Squat
description:
Load your desired weight on a barbell that is on a weight rack, about chest high. Position the bar on your shoulders, step away from the rack and stand with your hands supporting the bar and feet shoulder width apart.
Squat down by bending your hips back and letting your knees bend forward, keeping your back straight and knees pointed in the same direction as your feet. Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Extend your knees and hips until your legs are straight. Return and repeat.

name: Side Cable Raise
description:
Stand sideways next to a cable stack and attach the handle to the low pulley. With the machine to your right, grasp the handle with your right hand. Start with your left hand extended hanging down next to the machine.
Exhale as you pull your hand up until your hand is just over chest height. Lower and repeat. When you finish the set, repeat with your other arm.

name: Running
description: Start with a walk and gradually speed up until you are moving at a fast, steady pace.

name: Dumbbell Iron Cross
description:
Stand with your feet shoulder width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand. With your palms facing forward, outstretch your arms to the side making a letter "T."
Keeping a straight back, bend down at the knees as if you were sitting down in a chair. While you are descending, bring your arms in front of you until your hands are together and facing each other. Return and repeat.

name: Machine Lateral Raise
description:
Sit down at the machine. Grab the handles with your forearms resting against the pads.
Exhale as you raise your arms until your upper arms are horizontal. Return and repeat.

name: Cable Front Squat
description:
Attach a cable bar to the low pulley. Stand facing the machine with your feet a little wider than shoulder width apart. Bend your arms and place the bar in the in the folds of your elbows, placing your hands on opposite elbows.
Squat down keeping your back straight. Return to start position and repeat.

name: Barbell Front Squat
description:
Load your desired weight on a barbell that is on a weight rack, about chest high. Cross your arms and place your hands on top of the barbell while your upper arms are parallel to the floor.
Squat down by bending your hips back, letting your knees bend forward, keeping your back straight and knees pointed in the same direction as your feet. Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Extend your knees and hips until your legs are straight. Return and repeat.

name: Barbell Forward Lunge
description:
Load your desired weight on a barbell that is on a weight rack, about chest high. Place the barbell on your shoulders with your hands grabbing and supporting it. Stand with your feet shoulder width apart.
Lunge forward with your right leg. Lower your body by flexing your knee and hip in front, until your left knee is almost in contact with floor. Return and repeat by alternating lunge with opposite leg.

name: Standing Cable Crunch
description:
Stand with your back to the cable machine, one foot in front of the other, with the front leg slightly bent. With both hands, grab the rope and hold it over your shoulders with your elbows close to your body.
Bend down at your waist, pulling the rope with you so your body is perpendicular to the ground. Return to start position and repeat.

name: Cable Triceps Extension, Flat Bench
description:
Set up a flat bench facing away from the cable machine and attach a rope to the low pulley. Lie down with your body facing away from the machine. Grab the rope in a neutral grip and extend your arms so that they are straight up over your chest.
Inhale as you bring your arms back down until your hands are just above your forehead. Exhale, return and repeat.

name: Standing Adduction Machine
description:
Stand on the platform, grasp handles and place inner thigh against pad.
Move your leg side to side across your supporting leg. Return to starting position and repeat. When you finish continue with opposite leg.

name: Hanging Leg Raise, Toes to Bar
description:
Start by hanging from a chin-up bar, using either a wide grip or a medium grip.
Lift your extended legs up to the bar, making sure to curl the pelvis up. Return to starting position. Do not allow your legs to bend.

name: Superman
description:
Lie face down with your legs straight and your arms straight forward and raised.
Lift your legs and upper torso off the ground. Hold, then lower and repeat.

name: Barbell Backwards Lunge
description:
Load your desired weight on a barbell that is on a weight rack, about chest high. Place the barbell on your shoulders with your hands grabbing and supporting it and stand with your feet shoulder width apart.
Step back with your right leg while bending your supporting left leg. Plant the front of your right foot far back on floor. Lower your body by flexing your knee and hip of your left leg until the knee of your right leg is almost in contact with floor. Return and repeat by alternating lunge with opposite leg.

name: Hanging Leg Raise, Straight Legs
description:
Start by hanging from a chin-up bar, using either a wide grip or a medium grip.
Exhale as you raise your legs until they are parallel to the ground. Make sure that you're not cheating with the momentum.

name: Side Bridge with Leg Raise
description:
Lay on your side with one forearm flat on the ground. Prop your body off the floor, lifting your hips until your body is in a straight line from your ankles to your shoulders. Your feet should be stacked one on top of the other and your free hand on your hip.
Lift your hips up while lifting your top leg up in the air, keeping your legs and back straight. Lower to start position and repeat.

name: Cable Lat Pulldown Row, Seated Wide Overhand Grip
description:
Sit down at the machine, adjust the knee pad to your height and secure your knees under the padding. Grab the bar with your palms facing away from you slightly more narrow than shoulder width. Extend your arms all the way up and lean back slightly with your chest out.
Exhale as you bring the bar down while leaning back into a row. Inhale and lean back up as you bring the bar back up. Repeat.

name: Cable Calf Raise, Single Leg
description:
Attach a cable handle to a low pulley while standing with the front part of your right foot on the edge of an exercise step and your heel hanging off. Hold onto the support bar for balance while holding the cable handle.
Keeping your leg that is supporting you straight, flex your calf and raise yourself as high as you can before lowing back to your starting position and repeat.

name: Cable Abduction
description:
Stand in front of the low pulley facing one side. Attach cable cuff to your far ankle. Step out away from stack and grasp the bar. Stand on near foot and allow far leg to cross in front.
Move your leg sideways away from the low pulley using your hip. Return and repeat. Turn around and continue with opposite leg.

name: Dumbbell Triceps Extension, Incline Bench
description:
Lie on an incline bench and hold a dumbbell with two hands over your head with arms extended.
Inhale as you lower the dumbbell by bending your elbows until the dumbbell is behind your head. Keep your upper arms as still as possible. Exhale, return and repeat.

name: Cable Lat Pulldown, Normal Overhand Grip
description:
Sit down at the machine, adjust the knee pad to your height and secure your knees under the padding. Grab the bar about shoulder width apart.
Exhale as you bring the bar down. Inhale as you bring the bar back up. Repeat.

name: Bicycle Machine
description:
Sit down on the exercise bike, hold the grips and select "quick start" or enter program.
Pedal forward as you would on a bike while gripping the handles.

name: Bodyweight Flutter Kicks
description:
Lie face down on a flat bench with your legs straight and feet high off the floor. Hold on to the front edge of the bench.
Lift one leg, and then switch legs, alternating between them each time.

name: Bodyweight Pull Up, Neutral Grip
description:
Hold on to the pull up bar using the neutral grip handles (parallel bars) and grip them with your palms facing each other. Hang there with your body extended.
Exhale as you pull yourself up until your neck reaches the height of your hands. Inhale as you lower your body until your arms and shoulders are extended and repeat.

name: Cable Biceps Curl with Rope
description:
Attach a rope attachment to a low pulley and stand up straight, about a foot back away from the machine. Grip the rope in a neutral grip with your palms facing each other.
Keeping your arms close to your sides, curl the rope up, and return to the starting position and repeat.

name: Barbell Snatch Step 1 - Deadlift
description:
With feet flat beneath the bar, squat down and grab the bar with a overhand grip.
Exhale as you lift the bar by thrusting your hips and knees to full extension. Pull your shoulders back at top of lift and keep your back straight. Return and repeat.

name: Cable Pullover, Seated
description:
Sit on a flat bench with your feet flat on the floor. Grab the rope with both hands, keeping your arms straight. Make sure the bench is far enough away from the machine that there is some resistance in the cable.
Pull the rope down towards your knees, keeping your back and arms straight. Return to start position and repeat.

name: Incline Dumbbell Bench Press, Rotating Grip
description:
Lie down on an incline bench with a dumbbell in each hand resting on top of your thighs with your palms facing each other. Use your thighs to lift up the dumbbells one at a time so they are over your chest, shoulder width apart.
Breathe out and push the dumbbells up using your chest. As you press up, rotate your wrists so that when you fully extend your arms your grip is overhand rather than neutral. Return to start position as your rotate your hands back to a neurtral grip and repeating.

name: Incline Dumbbell Bench Press, Normal Grip
description:
Lie down on a bench with a dumbbell in each hand resting on top of your thighs with your palms facing each other. Use your thighs to lift up the dumbbells one at a time so they are over your chest, shoulder width apart.
Breathe out and push the dumbbells up using your chest.

name: Cable Triceps Kickback, Neutral Grip
description:
Stand facing the cable machine and bend down at your hips and knees, keeping your back straight. Grab the handle with one hand, palms facing your body. Bend your arm and keep your upper arm close to your body.
Extend your arm behind you by pressing your hand back and straightening your elbow. Keep your arm close to your body. Bend your arm to return to start position and repeat. Then switch sides.

name: Cable Fly, Single Arm
description:
Move the cables to a high position and stand with your feet hip distance apart. Grab the cable with one hand.
Keeping your arm straight and parallel to the floor, pull the cable out in front of your body so your hand is in the middle of your chest. Bring your arm back to start position and repeat.

name: Cable Biceps Drag Curl
description:
Stand up straight while holding a cable curl bar that is attached to a low pulley in your desired grip type.
While holding the upper arms still, curl the weights up to shoulder level, while slightly pulling your shoulders up and elbows back. Return to the starting position and repeat.

name: Chest Fly Machine
description:
Sit down at the machine with your back against the pad. Grab the handles while bracing your forearms against the pads.
Exhale as you press the handles together, inhale to return to start position and repeat.

name: Decline Dumbbell Pullover
description:
Lie down on a decline bench with a dumbbell securely grasped between both of your hands, palms facing each other. With your feet firmly planted on the floor or bench supports, raise the dumbbell up over your chest with your arms extended.
Keep your arms straight and lower the weight behind your head in an arc movement, as you breathe in. Extend until you feel a stretch in your chest, exhale as you return the weight to start position and repeat.

name: Chest Cable Overhead Shrug
description:
Place a flat bench perpendicularly and directly between two cable stacks. Place the handles on the low pulleys. Grab each handle and assume a position flat on your back on the bench. Start with your arms extended and your hands slightly wider than shoulder width apart.
Flex your chest and move your arms together so that your arms are slightly higher and your hands are closer together. The movement is small, so make sure that you feel the tension in your chest at the top of the movement. Return to start position and repeat.

name: Dumbbell Pullover
description:
Lie down on a flat bench with a dumbbell securely grasped between both of your hands, palms facing each other. With your feet firmly planted on the floor or bench supports, raise the dumbbell up over your chest with your arms extended.
Keep your arms straight and lower the weight behind your head in an arc movement, as you breathe in. Extend until you feel a stretch in your chest, and exhale as you return the weight to start position and repeat.

name: Barbell Snatch Step 2 - Deadlift into Shrug
description:
Start by grabbing a barbell with a wider than shoulder width, overhand grip. Keep your hips and knees slightly bent and your back flat.
Exhale as you push up and lift the bar with your legs, while at the same time bringing your torso to an upright position. Once you are standing, push your chest out and bring your shoulder blades back so you are standing upright at attention. Next, shrug your shoulders back before returning and repeating.

name: Row Machine
description:
Making sure that your feet are secure, bring your knees up and slide to the top of the machine. Grab the handle in an overhand grip. Make sure that your shirt is tucked in and nothing will get caught in the slide under your seat.
Exhale as you push back with your feet to slide to the back of the machine. Pull the handle throughout the movement, bringing it to just below your chest at the finish. Lead with your legs and make sure your legs are extended before you finish pulling the handle to your chest.

name: Cable Biceps Concentration Curl
description:
Attach the bar to the low pulley. Take a few small steps back from the machine, and squat all the way down and hold the bar in your desired grip type. Rest the top sections of your triceps on the tops of your knees.
Curl the bar up until eye-level and bring your arms back to start position with your arms extended.

name: Dumbbell Arm Circles
description:
Stand with your feet shoulder width apart holding two dumbbells in an overhand grip with your arms outstretched at your sides like a "T."
Gradually start rotating your arms forward, in a controlled circular motion. One circle is one repetition.

name: Cable Face Pull
description:
Stand facing the pulley machine with your feet shoulder width apart. Grab the rope with both hands and lean slightly back with a slight bend to your knees.
Pull the rope directly towards your face while separating your hands. Release back to start position and repeat.

name: Dragon Flags
description:
Lie on your back on a flat bench. Have both hands grab the sides of the bench by your head so your elbows are pointing upwards. Lift your legs slightly off the bench so your calves and lower thighs are not touching the bench.
Lift your legs and back off the bench as high as you can, keeping your legs straight. Only your shoulders should be left on the bench. Lower to start position and repeat.

name: Cable Biceps Curl, Single Arm, Overhand Grip
description:
Stand next to the cable machine with your feet shoulder width apart. With the hand closest to the machine, grab the handle, keeping your arm straight.
Bend your arm at the elbow, lifting your hand up towards your chest. Lower and repeat, then switch arms.

name: Reverse Cable Fly
description:
Stand with your feet shoulder width apart. Grab the left handle with your right hand and the right handle with your left hand, crossing your arms in front of you.
Pull the handles out to your sides, keeping your arms parallel to the floor. Return to start position and repeat.

name: Seated Cable Rows, High
description:
Sit on the bench facing the pulley machine. Attach the cable bar to the high pulley. Hold the bar with an overhand grip and extend your arms.
Exhale and as you pull back while sitting up straight with your elbows pointed out to your sides. Return to start position and repeat.

name: Lying Leg Raise
description:
Lie on your back, on the floor with legs stretched straight. Place your hands under your butt with your palms facing down.
Bring your knees up and keep your legs slightly bent. Return to start position and repeat.

name: Walking Lunge with Side Weights
description:
Stand with your feet shoulder width apart holding a weight in either hand.
With the weights secure in your hands, take a step forward into the lunge position with your right foot. Make sure that your right knee is on top of your right foot and not in front of it. Push up with your right foot and return to starting position, switch sides and repeat as you walk forward.

name: Dumbbell Reverse Fly, Seated
description:
Sit on the edge of a bench, bend over, and rest your torso on your thighs. Grasp the dumbbells in a neutral grip under your legs. Have a slight bend in your elbows.
Exhale as you lift your upper arms to the sides until your elbows are at shoulder height. Lower and repeat.

name: Cable Lat Pulldown Leaning Back, Wide Overhand Grip
description:
Sit down at the machine, adjust the knee pad to your height and secure your knees under the padding. Grab the bar with your palms facing away from you slightly more narrow than shoulder width. Extend your arms all the way up and lean back slightly with your chest out.
Exhale as you bring the bar down while leaning back into a row. Inhale and lean back up as you bring the bar back up. Repeat.

name: Dumbbell Lateral Raise
description:
Standing in a shoulder-width stance, grab a pair of dumbbells with palms facing inward and let them hang at your sides.
Raise your arms out to the sides until they're at shoulder level. Pause, then lower the weights back to the starting position. Repeat.

name: Lying Toe Touch
description:
Raise your legs straight up in the air until your feet are parallel with the floor. Reach your arms toward your feet with your head still on the floor.
Roll forward as you exhale, lifting your torso off the floor as you try to touch your toes with your fingers. Return to starting positon and repeat.

name: Cable Biceps Curl, Extended Low, Underhand Grip
description:
Stand with your feet slightly wider than shoulder width apart. Grab the handles with both hands, palms facing forward and arms straight.
Bend your arms at the elbow, bringing your hands up towards your shoulders. Lower to start position and repeat.

name: Torso Twist Machine
description:
Sit down at the torso twist machine, select your weight and place your arms on the padded rests for support. Ensure that your feet are secure.
Twist your body to the left and right until you complete your desired repetitions.

name: Barbell Thrust
description:
Start by sitting on the ground with a bench directly behind you. Have a loaded barbell over your legs. Roll the bar so that it is directly above your hips, and lean back against the bench, so that your shoulder blades are near the top of it and your arms are outstretched gripping the sides of the bench.
With your feet firmly planted on the ground, exhale and thrust your hips up vertically and extend as far as possible. Inhale as you lower and repeat.

name: Bodyweight Pull Up, Wide Grip
description:
Hold on to the pull up bar using a wide grip. Hang there with your body extended.
Exhale as you pull yourself up until your neck reaches the height of your hands. Inhale as you lower your body until your arms and shoulders are extended and repeat.

name: Dumbbell Triceps Extension (Decline Bench)
description:
Lie on a decline bench and hold a dumbbell with two hands over your head with arms extended.
Inhale as you lower the dumbbell by bending your elbows until the dumbbell is behind your head. Keep your upper arms as still as possible. Exhale, return and repeat.

name: Cable Triceps Side Extension, Behind Neck, Single Arm
description:
Stand with your feet shoulder width apart, with your side facing the machine. Using the hand farthest from the machine, grab the handle and bring it behind your head, with your elbow bent.
Straighten your arm out to your side, keeping it lifted. Return to start position and repeat.

name: Kettlebell 2 Handed Russian Swing
description:
Hold the kettlebell with two hands as you slightly bend at the hips keeping your back straight. The kettlebell should be just in front of your hips, between your legs.
