Thrust your hips forward and keep your knees straight so that the kettlebell is pushed forward and upward freely, until about shoulder height, while keeping your head forward and squeezing your glutes. Allow the kettlebell to swing back down. As the kettlebell approaches the lower swing, bend your hips and knees. Your forearm will make contact with your inner thigh, allowing the kettlebell to swing back under your hips. Repeat as many repetitions as you need to in a fluid motion.

name: Rope Cable Row, Incline Prone
description:
Lie face down on the incline bench and grab the rope with both hands.
Keeping your arms close to your side, pull the rope towards you by bending at the elbows and separating your hands.

name: Pushup, Narrow Grip
description:
Lie on the floor face down with your hands touching each other on the floor (create a diamond with your thumbs and forefingers) while holding your body off the ground with your arms extended.
Inhale and lower yourself downward until your chest nearly touches the floor. Exhale, return to starting position and repeat.

name: Dumbbell Calf Raise, Seated, Single Leg
description:
Sit down on a flat bench with an exercise step about a foot in front of you. Place the front of your foot on the step and rest a dumbbell on top of it.
Breathe out and raise your heel up as high as possible as you exhale. Slowly return to start position while stretching as far down as you can. Repeat and switch legs once you finish your set.

name: Cable Biceps Crossover, Low
description:
Stand with your feet slightly wider than shoulder width apart. Grab the handles with both hands, palms facing forward and arms straight. Step forward, creating tension in the cables.
Bend your arms at the elbow, crossing your arms to bring your hands up towards opposite shoulder. Lower to start position and repeat.

name: Cable Biceps Curl, Underhand Grip
description:
Stand with your feet shoulder width apart and grab the bar with both hands, palms facing you, while keeping your arms straight.
Bend your arms at the elbows, lifting your hands up towards your chest. Lower and repeat.

name: Oblique Leg Raise
description:
Position yourself in the captain's chair with your back and forearms against the padding and your hands grasping the handles. Hang your legs straight down.
Exhale as you pull your knees up to the right side as high as possible. Return to start position and repeat. When you have finished your set, switch sides.

name: Dumbbell Front Raise, Incline Prone
description:
With a dumbbell in each hand, lie face down on an incline bench with your shoulders near top of the bench. Let your arms extend and hang naturally in front of you with your palms facing backwards as you grip the dumbbells in an overhand grip.
Exhale as you raise the dumbbells in an arc to just above shoulder height. Return and repeat.

name: Hanging Leg Raise, Knees Up
description:
Start by hanging from a chin-up bar, using either a wide grip or a medium grip.
Raise your legs until the torso makes a 90-degree angle with the legs. Return slowly to start position and repeat.

name: Cable Lat Down-Flys
description:
Stand with your feet shoulder width apart. Grab the handles with each hand, palms facing down.
Pull the handles down behind you so your hands are at your butt. Return to start position and repeat.

name: Cable Good Morning
description:
Grab the bar with both hands and lean slightly backwards, keeping your legs straight and your feet pointing forward.
Bring the cable forward by bending over while keeping your back straight. Return to start position and repeat.

name: Cable Biceps Concentration Curl, Single Arm
description:
Attach a cable handle to the low pulley. Face away from the machine and grab the handle with your right hand in an underhand grip. Step forward with your left foot.
Exhale as you curl the handle up so your hand is touching your shoulder. Return to start position and repeat.

name: Burpee
description:
Stand upright with your arms to the sides.
Bend over and squat down with your hands outstretched in a pushup position. Kick your legs out and pull them back in before pushing yourself back to the starting position. Repeat.

name: Incline Dumbbell Pullover
description:
Lie down on an incline bench with a dumbbell securely grasped between both of your hands, palms facing each other. With your feet firmly planted on the floor or bench supports, raise the dumbbell up over your chest with a slight bend in your arms.
Keep your arms slightly bent and lower the weight behind your head, in an arc movement as you breathe in. Extend until you feel a stretch in your chest, exhale as you return the weight to start position and repeat.

name: EZ-Bar Biceps Top Half Curl, Preacher, Underhand Grip
description:
Sit down at the preacher bench and grab the bar using your desired grip type. With your upper arms and chest pressing against the preacher bench pad, extend your arms and hold the bar.
Keep your upper arms still, exhale, and curl the weights upwards while contracting your biceps. Lower the weights to starting position and repeat.

name: Dumbbell Bench Press, Normal Grip
description:
Lie down on a flat bench with a dumbbell in each hand resting on top of your thighs, with your palms facing each other. Use your thighs to lift up the dumbbells one at a time so they are over your chest, shoulder width apart.
Breathe out and push the dumbbells up using your chest.

name: Dumbbell Scarecrow, Incline Prone
description:
With a dumbbell in each hand, lie face down on an incline bench with your shoulders near top of the bench. Start with your upper arms stretched out to your sides and your forearms hanging down with your palms facing backwards.
Exhale as you twist your forearms and weights up in an arc so the weights are now in line with your head, and your wrists are facing forward. Return and repeat.

name: Cable Triceps Pushdown, Overhand Grip
description:
Attach the rope to the high pulley. Hold the rope in an overhand grip, facing the machine.
Exhale as you push down with your triceps, keeping your arms close to your sides. Return to start position and repeat.

name: Decline Cable Bench Press
description:
Place a decline bench perpendicularly and directly between two cable stacks. Place the handles on the low pulleys. Grab each handle and assume a position flat on your back on the bench. Start with your arms extended and your hands directly over your chest.
Press up while simultaneously pulling your hands together until the handles touch at the top. Lower and repeat.

name: Weighted Pull Up, Neutral Grip
description:
Add weight using a dip belt or by placing a dumbbell between your ankles. Hold on to the pull up bar using the neutral grip handles (parallel bars) and grip them with your palms facing each other. Hang there with your body extended.
Exhale as you pull yourself up until your neck reaches the height of your hands. Inhale as you lower your body until your arms and shoulders are extended and repeat.

name: Dumbbell Biceps Curl, Incline Prone, Neutral Grip
description:
With a dumbbell in each hand, lie face down on an incline bench with your shoulders near top of the bench. Let your arms extend and hang naturally in front of you with your palms facing each other.
Raise the dumbbells together and lower them back down while keeping your upper arms still.

name: Bodyweight Circle Pull Up
description:
Hang from the pull up bar with your palms facing each other.
Pull yourself in a circle, counter clockwise, with your neck up and over the pull up bar. Return to starting position by going back clockwise and repeat.

name: Cable Bench Press
description:
Place a flat bench perpendicularly and directly between two cable stacks. Place the handles on the low pulleys. Grab each handle and assume a position flat on your back on the bench.  Start with your arms extended and your hands directly over your chest.
Exhale and press up, while simultaneously pulling your hands together until the handles touch at the top. Lower and repeat.

name: Dumbbell Row, Incline Prone, Overhand Grip
description:
Lean into an inclined bench while holding two dumbbells in an overhand grip, with your palms facing you. Keep your toes on the floor to stabilize yourself. Keep your lower back straight and extend your arms down.
Exhale as you pull the weights up to chest height. Inhale as you lower and repeat.

name: Cable Lat Pulldown, Kneeling Alternating
description:
Kneel down between two pulley stacks with the cable handles attached to the high pulleys. Hold the handles and extend both arms.
Pull down one arm, and then alternate arms and repeat.

name: Hamstring Pullback Machine
description:
Start by adjusting the machine to your height and selecting your weight. Lie face down with the padded bar above your ankles and just below your calves. Stabilize yourself by gripping the handles of the machine.
Exhale and curl your legs in while pressing your ankles against the bar. Inhale as you extend your legs slightly back to starting position. You should feel tension in your muscles during the whole movement. Make sure your legs are touching the padded bar during the entire exercise.

name: Incline Bench Press, Normal Grip
description:
Lie back on an incline bench. Hold the bar with a normal grip straight over you.
Breathe in and slowly bring the bar down until it touches your chest. Exhale as you push the bar back to your starting position.

name: Seated Cable Rows, Middle
description:
Sit on the bench facing the pulley machine. Attach the cable bar to the middle pulley. Hold the bar with an overhand grip and extend your arms.
Exhale and as you pull back while sitting up straight with your elbows pointed out to your sides. Return to start position and repeat.

name: Weighted Hyperextension
description:
Place a weight plate at the bottom of the bench so you can grab it easily when you bend down for the first rep. Lie face down on a hyperextension bench, tucking your ankles securely under the footpads. Once you've adjusted the machine for your height, cross your arms in front of your chest keeping your body upright.
Inhale as you lower yourself as far as you can, only bending at the waist with a straight back, pick up your choice of weight and hold it until you finish your set. Exhale as you pull yourself back up and repeat.

name: Cable Shoulder Press, Military
description:
Stand between to cable stacks and attach the handles to the low pulleys. Stand with your forearms parallel to the floor and your hands raised with your palms facing forward.
Exhale, press your hands up and bring your arms back to the starting position and repeat.

name: Machine Row, Medium Grip
description:
Adjust the seat and chest pad to the correct height and select your weight. Grab the more narrow handles while keeping your back straight.
Exhale as you pull the handles towards you. Inhale as you return to start position and repeat.

name: Walking Lunge with Overhead Weight
description:
Hold a weight over your head and stand with feet shoulder width apart and your knees slightly bent.
With the weight secure in your hands over your head, take a step forward into the lunge position with your right foot. Make sure that your right knee is on top of your right foot and not in front of it. Push up with your right foot and return to starting position, switch sides and repeat as you walk forward.

name: Plank
description:
Get into a pushup position on the floor. Place your forearms on the ground with your elbows aligned below your shoulders, and your arms parallel to your body, at about shoulder-width distance apart.
Make sure your body is lifted and parallel to the floor for the duration of your plank.

name: Dumbbell Biceps Curl, Incline, Alternating, Underhand Grip
description:
Sit down on an inclined bench and hold one dumbbell in each hand in an underhand grip with your palms facing up.
Start by raising one dumbbell until it reaches shoulder level and lower it back down without jerking your upper body. Switch sides and repeat.

name: Dip Machine
description:
Sit down, select your weight and grab the handles with your elbows bent.
Exhale and push down with your triceps, while keeping your elbows close to your side. Inhale as you return to start position and repeat.

name: Hyperextension
description:
Lie face down on a hyperextension bench, tucking your ankles securely under the footpads. Once you've adjusted the machine for your height, cross your arms in front of your chest keeping your body upright.
Inhale as you lower yourself as far as you can, only bending at the waist with a straight back. Exhale as you pull yourself back up and repeat.

name: Hip Extension
description:
Lie on your back with one knee bent, and the other leg straight out hovering about an inch above the ground.
Lift your butt and hips off the ground, while lifting your straight leg up. Lower your leg and repeat, then switch legs.

name: Standing Abduction Machine
description:
Stand on the platform, grasp handles and place outer thigh against pad.
Move your leg as far as possible to the side (away from body). Return and repeat. Continue with opposite side.

name: Bench Press, Wide Grip
description:
Lie back on a flat bench. Hold the bar with a wide grip and hold the bar straight over you.
Breathe in and slowly bring the bar down until it touches your chest. Exhale as you push the bar back to your starting position.

name: EZ-Bar Triceps Extension
description:
Lie on a bench with an overhand grip on the EZ-bar. Position the bar over your forehead, with your arms extended.
Lower the bar by bending your elbows. When the bar nears your head, move elbows slightly back, just enough to allow the bar to clear around your head. Return and repeat.

name: EZ-Bar Biceps Curl, Underhand Narrow Grip
description:
Stand up straight with your legs shoulder width apart, while holding the bar in a narrow grip. Keep your elbows close to your sides.
Keep your upper arms still, exhale, and curl the bar upwards, while contracting your biceps. Lower the bar to starting position and repeat.

name: Kneeling Cable Crunch
description:
Kneel down on your knees in front of a high pulley with a rope attachment. Grab the rope and lower it down so your hands are behind your neck.
Bend down at your waist, pulling the rope with you, so your elbows are at your thighs. Return to start position and repeat.

name: Standing Cable Row, High
description:
Stand facing the pulley machine. Attach the cable bar to the high pulley. Hold the bar with an overhand grip and extend your arms.
Keeping your back straight, exhale as you bring the bar to your chest. Return to start position and repeat.

name: Front Cable Raise
description:
Attach a bar to the low pulley and grasp it in an overhand grip. Stand up straight with your feet shoulder width apart.
Exhale as you raise the bar up in an arc until it's above your head. Keep your arms extended and your back straight. Lower and repeat.

name: Pushup, Normal Grip
description:
Lie on the floor face down with your hands just wider than shoulder length apart, while holding your body off the ground with your arms extended.
Inhale and lower yourself downward until your chest nearly touches the floor. Exhale, return to starting position and repeat.

name: Reverse Cable Fly, On Flat Bench
description:
Position a flat bench between two cable stacks and attach the handles to the high pulleys. Grab the left handle with your right hand and vice versa with your arms extended and crossed across your chest.
Exhale as you pull your arms down to the opposite sides until your arms are straight and your hands are slightly below your torso. Return and repeat.

name: Dumbbell Bench Press, Narrow Grip
description:
Lie down on a flat bench with a dumbbell in each hand resting on top of your thighs with your palms facing each other. Use your thighs to lift up the dumbbells one at a time so they are over your chest, shoulder width apart. Hold the dumbbells in your desired grip, shoulder length apart.
Breathe out and push the dumbbells up using your chest.

name: Cable Lat Pulldown, Behind Neck, Wide Grip
description:
Sit down at the machine, adjust the knee pad to your height and secure your knees under the padding. Grab the bar with your palms facing away from you wider than shoulder width.
Exhale as you bring the bar down until it touches the back of your neck. Inhale as you bring the bar back up. Repeat.

name: Cable High Knees
description:
Attach a cable band to your right leg and hook it to the low pulley. Stand facing away from the machine.
Bring your right leg up, as if you were taking a running stride. Return and repeat.

name: Lateral Cable Raise, Single Arm
description:
Stand sideways next to a cable stack and attach the handle to the low pulley. With the machine to your right, grasp the handle with your left hand. Start with your left hand in front of your right thigh and your back straight.
Exhale as you raise your arm to the side until your left hand is extended over your head, and your hand is slightly to the right above your body. Lower and repeat. When you finish the set, repeat with your other arm.

name: Dumbbell Biceps Curl, Preacher, Single Arm
description:
Sit down at the preacher bench and place your upper arms against the arm pad, and grab a dumbbell in one hand.
Raise the dumbbell until your forearm is almost straight and then lower it back down after a short pause. Repeat and switch arms when you finish your set.

name: Dumbbell Biceps Curl, Incline, Neutral Grip
description:
Sit down on an inclined bench and hold one dumbbell in each hand in a neutral grip with your palms facing each other.
Raise both dumbbells together until they reach shoulder level, and lower them back down without jerking your upper body.

name: Weighted Side Bend
description:
Position yourself sideways on a hyperextension bench, with your right arm holding a plate weight. Make sure that your hips, feet and legs are secure against the appropriate padding and foot rests.
Lower your torso to the side as far as it can go while keeping your legs straight. Rise up so that your chest is above your torso. Return to start position and repeat. When you have finished your set, switch sides.

name: Lying Scissor Kicks
description:
Lay on the floor with your hands under your butt and your legs stretched out straight. With a slight bend at the knees, lift your legs up so your heels are slightly off the ground.
Lift your left leg up, while your right leg is lowered until the heel is about 2-3 inches from the ground. Switch movements by raising your right leg up and lowering your left leg.

name: Incline Bench Press, Narrow Grip
description:
Lie back on an incline bench. Hold the bar with a narrow grip straight over you.
Breathe in and slowly bring the bar down until it touches your chest. Exhale as you push the bar back to your starting position.

name: Mountain Climbers
description:
Get into a pushup position so your hands are directly under your chest at shoulder width apart, with straight arms.
Lift your right foot off the floor and slowly raise your knee as close to your chest as you can. Return to the starting position and repeat with your left leg.

name: Dumbbell Triceps Extension, Flat Bench, Single Arm, Cross Body
description:
Lie on a bench and hold a dumbbell with your left hand in a neutral grip with your left arm extended upwards. Lay your right hand across your stomach.
Inhale as you lower the dumbbell by bending your elbow, bring the dumbbell down sideways over your chest in an arc. Keep your upper arm as still as possible. Exhale, return and repeat, and switch sides when you finish this set.

name: Incline Dumbbell Front Raise
description:
Sit down on an incline bench holding a dumbbell in either hand in an overhand grip as your arms are held slightly lower than parallel to the floor.
Exhale as your lift up your arms until the dumbbells are slightly higher than your shoulders. Return and repeat.

name: Cable Triceps Extension, Incline Bench
description:
Set up an inclined bench facing away from the cable machine and attach a rope to the low pulley. Lie down with your body facing away from the machine. Grab the rope in a neutral grip and extend your arms so that they are straight up over your chest.
Inhale as you bring your arms back down until your hands are just above your forehead. Exhale, return and repeat.

name: Cable Lat Pulldown, Kneeling
description:
Kneel down between two pulley stacks with the cable handles attached to the high pulleys. Hold the handles and extend both arms.
Exhale as you pull down the cables in towards your shoulders. Inhale as you release and repeat.

name: Cable Lat Pulldown, Wide Grip
description:
Sit down at the machine, adjust the knee pad to your height and secure your knees under the padding. Grab the bar with your palms facing away from you, wider than shoulder width.
Exhale as you bring the bar down until it touches your upper chest. Inhale as you bring the bar back up. Repeat.

name: Standing Cable Row, Low
description:
Stand facing the pulley machine. Attach the cable bar to the low pulley. Hold the bar with an overhand grip and extend your arms.
Keeping your back straight, exhale as you bring the bar to your chest.

name: Lying Leg Raise, Straight Legs
description:
Lie on your back, on the floor with legs stretched straight.
Raise your legs as high as you can, keeping them straight throughout. Return them to the floor in a controlled manner, and repeat.

name: Dumbbell Triceps Kickback, Bench, Neutral Grip
description:
Put your right leg on the top of a flat bench, while placing your hand at the end of the bench for support. Grab the dumbbell with one hand in a neutral grip (palms facing your stomach). Keep your lower back straight. Start with your forearm facing the floor and your upper arm parallel to the floor.
Exhale as you extend your arm back in an arc while keeping your upper arm still. Inhale as you lower and repeat. Switch sides when you finish.

name: Side Bridge
description:
Lay on your side with one forearm flat on the ground and your hips touching the ground. Your feet should be stacked one on top of the other and your free hand on your hip.
Lift your hips off the ground as high as is comfortable.

name: Barbell Shoulder Press, Behind Neck, Wide Grip
description:
Sit down on a shoulder press bench and grab onto the bar.
Keeping a straight back, exhale and press the bar upward until your arms are extended overhead. Lower to your shoulders behind your head and repeat.

name: Incline Bench Press, Wide Grip
description:
Lie back on an incline bench. Hold the bar with a wide grip straight over you.
Breath in and slowly bring the bar down until it touches your chest. Exhale as you push the bar back to your starting position.

name: Cable Adduction
description:
Stand in front of a low cable with one leg facing the cable and the other one away. Attach the ankle cuff to the leg closest to the cable. Stand on the foot that does not have the ankle cuff and allow the free leg to be pulled towards the pulley.
Cross your leg with the ankle cuff in front of your standing leg, while keeping your hips and upper body squared front. Bring your leg back to start position and repeat.

name: Seated Cable Crunch
description:
Sit on a bench with your back facing the high pulley. With both hands, grab the rope, palms facing each other, and bring the rope down so your hands are at your neck, below your ears.
Bend down at your waist, pulling the rope with you, so your elbows are by your thighs. Return to start position and repeat.

name: Barbell Clean & Jerk Step 1 - Clean
description:
Stand over barbell with the front of your feet positioned under the bar, slightly wider apart than hip width. Squat down and grip the bar with an overhand grip. Position your shoulders over the bar with your back arched tightly. Keep your arms straight with your elbows lined up over the bar.
Lift the bar up off floor by extending your hips and knees. As bar reaches your knee height, aggressively lift your shoulders while keeping barbell close to your thighs. When the barbell passes mid-thigh, allow it to touch your thighs. Thrust upward extending your body. Shrug shoulders and pull barbell upward with arms, allowing your elbows to flex out to sides while keeping the bar close to body. Pull your body under the bar, while rotating your elbows around bar. Catch the bar on shoulders while moving into squat position. When you reach the bottom of your squat, immediately thrust up. Return and repeat.

name: Dumbbell Bench Press, Rotating Grip
description:
Lie down on a flat bench with a dumbbell in each hand resting on top of your thighs, with your palms facing each other. Use your thighs to lift up the dumbbells one at a time so they are over your chest, shoulder width apart. Hold the dumbbells with your palms facing each other.
Breathe out and push the dumbbells up using your chest. As you press up, rotate your wrists so that when you fully extend your arms your grip is overhand rather than neutral. Return to start position as you rotate your hands back to a neutral grip and repeating.

name: Seated Cable Rows, Low
description:
Sit on the bench facing the pulley machine. Attach the cable bar to the low pulley. Hold the bar with an overhand grip and extend your arms.
Exhale and as you pull back while sitting up straight with your elbows pointed out to your sides. Return to start position and repeat.

name: Lying Reverse Crunch Up
description:
Lay on the floor with your hands under your butt and your legs stretched out straight.
Lift your legs up and bring your knees toward to your chest, while crunching up and placing maximum tension on your lower abs. Return to start position and repeat.

name: Incline Cable Bench Press
description:
Place an incline bench perpendicularly and directly between two cable stacks. Place the handles on the low pulleys. Grab each handle and assume a position flat on your back on the bench. Start with your arms extended and your hands directly over your chest.
Press up while simultaneously pulling the hands together until your handles touch at the top. Lower and repeat.

name: Incline Dumbbell Bench Press, Wide Grip
description:
Lie down on an incline bench with a dumbbell in each hand resting on top of your thighs with your palms facing each other. Use your thighs to lift up the dumbbells one at a time so they are over your chest, shoulder width apart. Hold the dumbbells in your desired grip about 6 inches wider than shoulder length apart.
Breathe out and push the dumbbells up using your chest.

name: Leg Raise, Knees Bent
description:
Position yourself in a captain's chair with your back and forearms on the pads, and your hands gripping the handles. Bend your knees and lift your legs up, so that you are suspended in a sitting position.
Exhale as you raise your legs as high as you can. Return to start position and repeat. Make sure that you're not cheating with the momentum.

name: Machine Shoulder Press
description:
Set the weight, sit down, grab the handles and make sure your feet are solid on the floor.
Exhale and press the handles up until your arms are extended. Lower, while keeping the weight stack in the air for resistance throughout the entire exercise, and repeat.

name: Crunch
description:
Lie on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the floor, hip-width apart. Place your hands behind your head without pulling on your neck.
Curl up and forward so that your head, neck, and shoulder blades lift off the floor and then lower slowly back down and repeat.

name: Dumbbell Row, Incline Prone, Neutral Grip
description:
Lean into an inclined bench while holding two dumbbells in a neutral grip with your palms facing each other. Keep your toes on the floor to stabilize yourself. Keep your lower back straight and extend your arms down.
Exhale as you pull the weights up to chest height. Inhale as you lower and repeat.

name: Cable Lat Pulldown Leaning Back, Narrow Underhand Grip
description:
Sit down at the machine, adjust the knee pad to your height and secure your knees under the padding. Grab the bar in a narrow, underhand grip with your palms facing you slightly more narrow than shoulder width. Extend your arms all the way up and lean back.
Exhale as you bring the bar down until it touches your upper chest. Inhale as you bring the bar back up. Repeat.

name: Dumbbell Wrist Curl
description:
Stand up straight with a dumbbell in each hand in an underhand grip with your palms facing forward. Keep the dumbbells secure, but hold them with your fingers more than squeezing them with your palms.
Curl your wrists upwards while you exhale. Inhale and lower your wrists back to your starting position. Repeat while keeping your forearms still.

name: Cable Triceps Extension, Decline Bench
description:
Set up a decline bench facing away from the cable machine and attach a rope to the low pulley. Lie down with your body facing away from the machine. Grab the rope in a neutral grip and extend your arms so that they are straight up over your chest.
Inhale as you bring your arms back down until your hands are just above your forehead. Exhale, return and repeat.

name: Dumbbell Biceps Curl, Incline Prone, Underhand Grip
description:
With a dumbbell in each hand, lie face down on an incline bench with your shoulders near the top of the bench. Let your arms extend and hang naturally in front of you with your palms facing forward.
Raise the dumbbells together until your forearms are perpendicular to the floor, and lower them back down while keeping your upper arms still.

name: Incline Dumbbell Fly
description:
Lie down on an incline bench with a dumbbell in each hand, resting on top of your thighs with your palms facing each other. Use your thighs to lift up the dumbbells with your palms facing each other and extend your arms out to your sides with a slight bend in your elbows and stretch in your chest.
Exhale and bring the dumbbells up and together in a wide arc. Return to starting position and repeat.

name: Upright Cable Row
description:
Attach the cable bar to the low pulley and grab it in an overhand grip with both hands. Stand with your feet shoulder width apart.
Pull the bar up, with your elbows out to the sides until the bar is at about chin height. Return and repeat.

name: Cable Rotation, Internal
description:
Stand sideways next to a cable machine with the machine on your right and attach the handle to the medium pulley. Grab the handle with your right forearm extended towards the machine.
Exhale as you use your shoulders to twist the handle over your torso in front of you. Return and repeat.

name: Cable Side Bend
description:
Stand with your feet shoulder width apart, your side facing the machine. Grab the handle with one hand, palms facing your body.
Lean to one side, bending at the hips. Leave your free hand by your side. Repeat, bending from side to side.

name: Cable Triceps Extension, Kneeling, on Bench
description:
Set up a bench near the cable machine and attach a rope to the high pulley. Hold the rope in the neutral grip and face away from the machine and kneel with your elbows bent against the bench and your forearms facing up towards the high pulley.
Exhale as you keep your arms close to your head and push the rope down in an arc until your arms are extended and parallel to the floor. Inhale, return and repeat.

name: Stability Ball Jackknife
description:
Place your stomach on the ball and roll forward until your hands touch the floor. Walk your hands in front of you until your shins are on the ball. Keep your hands a bit wider than shoulder width apart, in a pushup position.
Without moving your arms or shoulders, use your feet to roll the ball towards your chest, by bending your knees. Straighten your legs and bring the ball back to starting position and repeat.

name: Cable Triceps Kickback, Overhand Grip
description:
Stand facing the cable machine and bend down at your hips and knees, keeping your back straight. Grab the handle with one hand, palms facing down. Bend your arm and keep the upper arm close to the body.
Extend your arm behind you by pressing your hand back and straightening your elbow. Keep your arm close to your body. Bend your arm to return to start position and repeat. Then switch sides.

name: Chest Fly Machine, Straight Arm
description:
Adjust the seat so that when the handles are grasped, your arms are outstretched and parallel to the ground.
Exhale and squeeze your arms together until your arms meet in front of your face.

name: Russian Twist
description:
Lay back with your legs in the air and your hands behind your head.
Keeping your legs in the air, pull your body up as you would in a normal situp, but at the top of the movement, twist your torso right and left before straightening out, returning and repeating.

name: Reverse Cable Fly, Seated
description:
Position a bench between two cable stacks and attach the handles to the high pulleys. Grab the left handle with your right hand and vice versa with your arms crossed across your chest.
Exhale as you pull your your arms down to the opposite sides until your arms are straight and slightly behind your body. Return and repeat.

name: Bodyweight Row, Inverted
description:
Grip a bar, or set of rings, that is about waist high on a rack or Smith machine, with a wide overhand grip. Hang straight under the bar with your heels stabilizing you on the ground. Fully extend your arms.
Exhale as you pull yourself up so that your chest touches the bar. Inhale as you return to starting position and repeat.

name: Barbell Snatch Step 3 - Deadlift into Highpull
description:
Start by grabbing a barbell with a wider than shoulder-width, overhand grip. Keep your hips and knees slightly bent and your back flat.
Exhale as you push your feet into the floor and pull the barbell up to rest just above your knees. Extend your knees and thrust your hips, as you explosively drive into an upright row. Return and repeat.

name: Dip, Freestyle
description:
Grab the handles of a dip station and lift yourself until your arms are extended and your body is straight up and down.
Inhale as you lower your body until your upper arms are parallel to the floor. Exhale as your use your upper body to push yourself back up to your starting position.

name: Cable Hip Extension Backwards
description:
Attach a cable band to your right leg and hook it to the low pulley. Stand facing the machine with your arms on the stabilizing bars.
Keep your knees slightly bent and your core tight as you slowly kick your right leg back in an arc. Slowly return to start position and repeat.
